```python
# Convert feet to units
radius_units = 10 * 3

drone.curve_xyz_speed(radius_units, 0, 0, 0, radius_units, 0, 10)
drone.curve_xyz_speed(0, radius_units, 0, -radius_units, 0, 0, 10)
drone.curve_xyz_speed(-radius_units, 0, 0, 0, -radius_units, 0, 10)
drone.curve_xyz_speed(0, -radius_units, 0, radius_units, 0, 0, 10)
```

To fly up 6 feet, you can convert the distance to units using the conversion factor provided earlier. Assuming 1 unit is equal to 1/3 of a foot, you can calculate the number of units as follows:

```python
distance_ft = 6
distance_units = distance_ft * 3
drone.move_up(distance_units)
```

Please note that the drone may have limitations on the maximum height it can reach, so make sure to check the drone's specifications and adjust the distance accordingly.
